import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['delay'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, ax=ax, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(x=data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["delay"].median():.2f}')
    ax.axvline(x=data['delay'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["delay"].mean():.2f}')
    ax.set_xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of flight delays?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['distance'], ax=ax, color='lightblue')
    ax.axvline(data['distance'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["distance"].median():.2f} miles')
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?')
    plt.xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data = data.groupby('origin').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = data.sort_values('counts', ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="origin", y="counts", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set(xlabel='Origin Airport', ylabel='Number of Flights')
    ax.axhline(y=data['counts'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max: {:.2f}'.format(data['counts'].max()))
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data = data.groupby('destination').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = data.sort_values('counts', ascending=False)
    sns.barplot(x='destination', y='counts', data=data, color='b')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.axhline(y=data['counts'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max Count: {:.2f}'.format(data['counts'].max()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the most common destination airport?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y=data.index, data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of flight dates?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
